  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I want to easily understand `specs` error (both in terminal and in app) \r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\nErrors generated by `specs` are pretty hard to decypher (especially because of how we use specs).\r\n\r\n![specs](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/359723/34108257-b3ba97dc-e3ff-11e7-9c0f-b17a9dbbd6c6.png)\r\n\r\nIt would help to get human friendly error messages (in terminal too).\r\n\r\nSome libraries that might help with that:\r\n\r\n* https://github.com/bhb/expound\r\n* https://github.com/athos/Pinpointer\r\n* https://github.com/alexanderkiel/phrase",
